# Railway Quick Deploy Reference

## Required Files (All Present ✓)
- Procfile
- railway.json
- nixpacks.toml
- runtime.txt
- requirements.txt

## Railway Configuration

### 1. Root Directory
Set in Railway Settings: `backend`

### 2. Environment Variables
```
DATABASE_URL=<your-supabase-url>
GEMINI_API_KEY=<your-gemini-key>
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
ENVIRONMENT=production
```

### 3. Build Command
```bash
pip install --upgrade pip && pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Start Command
```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT --workers 2
```

## Deployment Checklist
1. ✓ Commit code to GitHub
2. □ Create Railway project
3. □ Set Root Directory to "backend"
4. □ Add environment variables
5. □ Deploy
6. □ Test health endpoint
7. □ Update frontend with Railway URL

## Test Commands
```bash
# Health check
curl https://YOUR-APP.up.railway.app/health

# API docs
curl https://YOUR-APP.up.railway.app/docs
```

## Troubleshooting
- If build fails: Check Root Directory = "backend"
- If app won't start: Check environment variables
- If 502 error: Check logs for port binding
- If 500 error: Check DATABASE_URL and API keys
